JOHANNESBURG - Mamelodi Sundowns on Tuesday announced the release of veteran midfielder Teko Modise from his contract.The club said on their website that Modise leaving the club would pave a way for him to negotiate a good contract for himself at this stage of his football career.READ: Modise gunning for more accoladesThe club said, Mamelodi Sundowns is grateful to Teko for his many years of loyal service to the club and wishes him everything of the very best. Modise played an important part in winning two PSL titles and the CAF Championship as well as the CAF Super Cup.eNCA